data.title: A Happy Hour Gem
data.text: Surprised that this restaurant was so good.  Happy hour appetizers are a steal and there's a lot of choices.  Had the seafood dip very nice with pita.  Had a couple of great IPAs before dinner at HH and felt little pain.  Dinner was meatloaf-good not great. Smothered in a ketchup gravy that was forgettable.  Told the waitress the meal was missing something and then it hit me- a vegetable.  So I ordered the crispy Brussels sprouts in bacon and it was the best part of the meal, just superb.  Overall a nice atmosphere for friends to get together after work and have some beers and food.  Remember to come here between 5-7pm for some tasty cheap appetizers and drink specials.

data.title: Closed, as of Nov 6, 2016
data.text: Well, it will be missed. Word on the street has it that the rent got too high, even for a busy place like this. They supposedly will join forces with Smoke BBQ next door, and re-open bigger and better in May 2017. Let's hope so. The new tenant is supposed to be a burger chain.

data.title: Delicious!
data.text: Tryst is a very good restaurant with great ambiance and delicious food. The crispy gulf shrimp are amazing, although as it says in the menu is a very small portion. The spring pea humus is delicious (the pita bread was not the best, it could've been fresher). The Pad Thai and Cedar River Hanger Steak were amazing! Service could be better. There was a lot of people but they should have more waiters to have a service in line with the restaurants quality.

data.title: Worse than horrible....
data.text:
While there are only a small handful of Atlantic avenue restaurants that are worthwhile... this is certainly not one of them. While the perception from standing outside or inside, is that of charming and inviting, one attempt at a meal in this place will quickly alert you to the fact that it is anything but the fact. The biggest flaw is the lack of any management. The blond hostess is a disaster. She has no business making any attempt at trying to manage seating customers. The waitress was not informed on the menu or the nightly specials. This too is the lack of proper training and management. The only thing that could have saved this establishment would have been the food and that too was an epic failure. 

All in all. There is no saving this place. Dont even bother going here. Go find one of the more enjoyable restaurants on the block. A word to the owner. Wake up.

data.title: Exceeded expectations
data.text:
We had been skipping this restaurant every weekend, thinking that the dinner menu was a little too trendy. But I was wrong. 

Made a reservation on Yelp (sorry TripAdvisor!) but then called direct to see if we could come just a little later. Even though they appeared to be booked-up for night, the hostess made it happen for us. Ate inside in a date-night friendly atmosphere. All wait staff were attentive, maybe a little inexperienced, but very pleasant. 

Nice beer list. All of the food was delicious and nicely presented. We will definitely go again. One of the better places that I have been to on Atlantic Ave.

data.title: Hidden gem
data.text: Got a Groupon here before a trip, very quirky and fun! The waitress was super nice, the inside was a darker funkier style, outside was a cool terrace with a big colorful mural.  I had the Pad Thai which is supposed to be very popular and let me tell you, it was the BEST I've ever had!! I almost ate the whole thing, with the help of my husband...it was massive.  My husband had the fish tacos, also great. Overall, great place, cool old timey looking bar if you're into eclectic gastropubs, its your place!

data.title: Good service and good food!!
data.text: Had a nice meal for our anniversary with corkage fee waived.  We liked it so mech, we got a gift card for friends.

data.title: Great Seafood.
data.text: Down in Delray for an anniversary, and we had a table in outside in the back of the patio area. The service was excellent and the wait staff explained the menu very well. The Grilled Mahi Mahi is the best fist I have ever had. We will certainly go back here again if we get back down to Delray in the furture!

data.title: Off night?
data.text:
Had the seafood dip but it was super dry and barely spreadable..rec by waitress.
Had rib eye special of nite..needed more draining but the cheese kale was great.
Brownie with ice cream was a super hard Brownie ( almost like a thick cracker) with fast melting vanilla ice cream ( It was hot outside) but didn't win us over.
This is my 4 time here and it will be
 awhile till I get it again. First " off" meal ever had here.

data.title: Brunch is DELICIOUS!!
data.text: Came with a group of 8 - excellent wait staff and Brunch was really good - we got french toast of the table and it was YUMMY - avocado toast was excellent!!

data.title: Based on the food we had it's 5 star
data.text:
I thought it had a good pub like atmosphere and a very interesting menu. The watermelon and belly of pork salad was unique and amazing. 
The steak was good enough.  My wife asked for plain grilled mahi and mashed potato and was happy with that which was a relief. 
Our server Hassan was a gentleman and contributed greatly to our enjoyment of the meal.

data.title: Hipster Vibe with excellent food and service
data.text:
Fun farm house meets steampunk atmosphere.  The food is creative and well executed.  Staff is accommodating and educated.   Overall an excellent restaurant.   
Fried Chicken with a runny egg alludes to the kitchens love and understanding of food.  Sunday Brunch on the patio is nice.

data.title: Enjoyable
data.text: My husband and I went here for dinner and we really enjoyed our meal. Service was great and our water glasses were never empty. We both had special cocktails that were delicious and strong! We went on a Wednesday and it was $5 burger night, my husband got the burger and he loved it. I went with the mahi fish tacos which were delicious as well. Portions were big and the prices were decent. I would definitely go here again.

data.title: Great foods, drinks & service
data.text: All foods & drinks are delicious.  Their specials change daily which keep the dining experience interesting.  Hostesses are welcoming.  Servers are quick & attentive.  Tryst has great brunch menu.  Chili soup with corn tortillas has a great kick to start your meal if you love spices.  Falafel pita is served with a huge side salad.  Chicken chop with mash potatoes are served hot & appetizing.  Cheese platter consists for different delicious cheeses from around the world; served with crackers.  We requested bread with cheese platter, but server said that restaurant does not have bread.

data.title: Great food, awesome beer, friendly service
data.text:
We went to tryst last night and had a great time. I had a delicious floridian hefeweizen and a new England corn chowder. The tuna poke lettuce wraps were memorable.
Great atmosphere. 
Will be back soon

data.title: Consistently great
data.text: My husband and I have a very special place in our hearts for this place. Not only is the food and service always consistently good, we met here on our first date and he proposed to me at this restaurant. Our fave is the buffalo pork belly and the wine and margaritas are great. After eating hours, it's a great bar to hang out and have drinks. It does get very busy so get there a little early to grab a seat at the bar

data.title: Happening Place
data.text:
Visited for the first time last night. I tried the BBQ Brisket special for $20. Very unique. Similar to both corned beef and pastrami. 
My wife had grilled mahi for $25. Very tasty. 
Although they have a nice wine list, we brought our own 2010 Shafer One Point Five and paid the $20 corkage fee.  Wine mark ups are your typical 2-3 times retail. 
Service was very good. 
The bar was packed, as was the outdoor eating area.

data.title: American Tapas
data.text:
Tryst is a gastropub, whatever that is. Mostly small portion to share, American tapas.

I started with a very good "Angry Pig" Sliders,Sicilian Pulled Pork, Orange Marmalade, Pickled Fresno Chilies, Fennel Slaw, Basil for $4 each. Next I ordered the Housemade Chorizo Burger, Avocado mayo, cheddar, bibb lettuce, tomato, red onion & charred habanero hot sauce. Definitely different and good.

My wife ordered the "Sol Kitchen" Mahi Tacos,  Napa cabbage slaw, tomato, guacamole, house mojo . Too spicy and she sent it back and ordered the Pontano Arugula salad, Laura Chenel goat cheese, hazelnuts, roasted oyster mushrooms, truffle-fig vinaigrette which is available in a half portion.

data.title: The place for Pork!
data.text: We enjoyed a delightful dinner in their patio and had delish salads and pork medallions.  Portions were very filling!

data.title: Nice Brunch on Sunday
data.text: We visited Tryst for brunch on Sunday and they have a nice brunch menu with unlimited mimosa's for $12.  The only thing I would suggest improving is to serve the mimosa's a little colder as my first one was luke warm.  We ordered the Tryst burger which was really great with lot's of flavor and the fish tacos which are one of their signature dishes.  They sometimes have live music (guitar, sax, etc.) which also adds a nice ambiance.  The service is also very attentive and friendly.
